Start

Input the values start and stop.

Set found = False.

Repeat for each number num from start to stop.

Check if num > 1.

Repeat for i from 2 to √num.

Check condition:

If num % i == 0 → break (number is not prime).

If no divisor is found, then:

Print num

Set found = True.

After the loop, check found.

If found == False → Print "No primes".

Stop
